# Code comments policy

## Language

- **All new and retained comments** (including `//`, `/* */`, `/** */`, and inline CSS comments in Vue SFCs) must be **English** only.
- **Do not** put Ukrainian or Russian prose in comments. Product-facing strings stay in their i18n/data files per locale rules; comments are for maintainers.

## When to comment (keep)

Keep a comment only when it carries information that is **not obvious from names/types** and one of:

- **Invariant or contract** (ordering, lifecycle, idempotency, “must not” rules).
- **Non-obvious bug workaround** (browser/engine quirk, race, stack overflow link, ticket id).
- **Security or authority** note (why something is validated server-side, why a guard exists).
- **Performance or coupling** note that would be dangerous to “simplify” without reading history.

Prefer **one short block** over many scattered lines.

## When not to comment (delete)

- Restates the next line of code (“increment counter”, “return result”).
- Restates obvious control flow (“loop over items”, “if null return”).
- Section banners that duplicate file structure (`// --- utils ---`).
- Duplicated doc already in types, JSDoc on the public API, or README.
- Commented-out dead code — **remove the code** or restore it; do not leave blocks disabled in comments.

## Edits in existing files

- If a comment is useful but not English: **translate** to concise English or **delete** if redundant after translation.
- If cleaning a file: aim to remove **most** comments and leave **only** the categories above — do not strip comments that document WebRTC/realtime ordering, billing edge cases, or layout bugs without replacing them with an equally clear English line.

## Style

- Imperative or neutral factual tone; no chatty filler.
- No secrets, tokens, or PII in comments.

## Bulk maintenance (repo)

- `npm run comments:prune` runs `scripts/prune-low-signal-comments.mjs` on `apps/*` and `packages/*` (skips `*.d.ts`). It removes low-signal comments but **keeps** matches for directives, URLs, TODO/FIXME, and realtime/security keywords (see script). Re-run `npm run lint`, `npm run test:ci`, and `npm run build -w client` after changes; fix any newly surfaced `vue-tsc` issues with proper types instead of relying on removed comments.
